VL  - 34
IS  - 3
SP  - 349
EP  - 354
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/03/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(87)90017-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900170
AB  - This note reconsiders the general class of Sargan densities studied by Goldfeld and Quandt (1981) and Missiakoulis (1983) in the context of approximating normal densities in regression models. Some errors in these papers are pointed out and the Sargan densities are re-computed. To the contrary of Missiakoulis' conclusion, the first two order densities are not the best choice. Higher-order densities are better approximations, though the best choice appears to be the second-order density based on the Goldfeld-Quandt criteria.
