VL  - 34
IS  - 3
SP  - 361
EP  - 372
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/03/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(87)90019-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407687900194
AB  - Extended Linear Expenditure System (ELES) household scales use the income variable of the household in identifying a system of Engel curves. Income data in household surveys may contain declaration errors which result in the errors-in-variables problem. A composite error distribution which incorporates both measurement and declaration errors into the model is proposed and the ELES scales are re-estimated. They are found to be sensitive to income declaration errors and biased measures of household welfare.
ER  - 
